<template>
  <hero :title="title" :viewName="viewName" :links="links" :tagline="tagline" />
</template>

<script>
import hero from '@/components/hero.vue'

export default {
  name: 'about',
  components: {
    hero
  },
  data () {
    return {
      title: 'About Me',
      viewName: 'home',
      links: ['Portfolio', 'Resume', 'Contact'],
      tagline: 'I am a Front End Web Developer in Cleveland, Ohio. I have a love for creating clean and functional code that translates to beautiful user experiences.'
    }
  },
  metaInfo: {
    title: 'About', // set a title
    titleTemplate: '%s  ← Dasha Utyuzh', // title is now "My Example App  ← My Site!"
    htmlAttrs: {
      lang: 'en',
      amp: undefined // "amp" has no value
    },
    meta: [
      {name: 'description', content: 'Front End Web Developer in Cleveland, Ohio'}
    ]
  }
}
</script>
